parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in repairing the Takata airbag recall can lead to serious injury or death in the event of a crash, as the faulty airbag inflators can explode and send shrapnel into the passenger compartment.
symptoms: None
as this is a recall issue rather than a symptom-based problem. However
the risk of injury or death is present if the vehicle is involved in a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbags to deploy in a crash can lead to serious injury or death, as the occupants of the vehicle may not be adequately protected.
symptoms: The airbags did not deploy in a crash
resulting in injuries or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Failure due to ABS and ECM Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brakes can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when the vehicle is unable to stop in time.
symptoms: The brakes fail to engage
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal touches the floor
the brakes make a loud squeaking noise
the vehicle takes longer to stop
inconsistent braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when the vehicle surges forward unexpectedly.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal surges forward
the vehicle accelerates unexpectedly
the gas pedal is sensitive.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive engine oil consumption can lead to premature engine wear, increased emissions, and potentially cause engine failure, which can result in costly repairs or even accidents.
symptoms: The oil level warning light is illuminated
the oil level drops rapidly between oil change intervals
the vehicle consumes excessive amounts of oil
the oil level needs to be topped off frequently (e.g.
every 2 weeks)
the vehicle requires adding 1.5 quarts or more of oil to maintain a normal level.
